Interface BenchmarkDataSource<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Chronix, GraphiteInterface, InfluxDB, KairosDB, OpenTsdbInterface

    public interface BenchmarkDataSource<T>
    Created by mcqueen666 on 08.08.16. Interface implementations have to implement this interface. BenchmarkDataSource jar packed has to be rolled out to user and be used as dependency for TSDB implementations

    • Method Detail

      • setup

        boolean setup(java.lang.String ipAddress,
              int portNumber)
        Setup the implementation on given server (e.g. create database ...)
        Parameters:
        ipAddress - the database server ip address.
        portNumber - the port number on which the database system is available. (docker container)
        Returns:
        true if setup was successful.
        API Note:
        This method will NOT be part of the benchmark measurement.
        Implementation Note:
        Keep track of ipAddress and portNumber!

      • clean

        boolean clean()
        Cleanses the database on given server. Resets the database to the setup() condition.
        Returns:
        true if clean-up was successful.
        API Note:
        This method will NOT be part of the benchmark measurement.

      • shutdown

        void shutdown()
        Shut down established connections. (if needed)

      • ableToMeasureExternalDirectory

        boolean ableToMeasureExternalDirectory()
        Decide if the storage measurement should be done IN the docker container or on external mapped folder on the host.
        Returns:
        true if the host could measure size of getMappedStorageDirectoryPath() by it self, or false if host has to measure the getStorageDirectoryPath() IN the docker container.
        API Note:
        the OS of the docker container must have the coreutils du command, otherwise setup external mapped folder and return true. (host does also need coreutils du command)
        Implementation Note:
        also create the mapped folder here!

      • getStorageDirectoryPath

        java.lang.String getStorageDirectoryPath()
        Returns:
        the absolute storage directory path to a TSDB implementation IN the docker container.

      • getMappedStorageDirectoryPath

        java.lang.String getMappedStorageDirectoryPath()
        Returns:
        the absolute storage directory path on the host (outside the TSDB docker container) which is mapped to the storage directory IN the docker container. (docker -v host/dir:/container/dir)

      • writeCachesToDisk

        void writeCachesToDisk()
        Writes cached data to disk.
        API Note:
        This method will be called just before the disk usage will be estimated after a series of queries was performed.

      • getQueryObject

        T getQueryObject(BenchmarkQuery benchmarkQuery)
        Generates the query string that will be performed with performQuery().
        Parameters:
        benchmarkQuery - the query representation.
        Returns:
        the query object which is needed for performing the query.
        API Note:
        This method will NOT be part of the benchmark measurement.

      • importDataPoints
